e\n|pictype=art\n|no1=712\n|name1=Bergmite\n|type1-1=Ice\n|evo1={{bag|Rare Candy}} <br>{{color2|000|Level|Level 37}}\n|no2=713\n|name2=Avalugg\n|type1-2=Ice}}\n\n===Sprites===\n{{Spritebox/Header|type=ice}}\n{{Spritebox/NA|gen=VI}}\n{{Spritebox/6|ndex=713}}\n{{Spritebox/7|ndex=713}}\n{{Spritebox/Footer|713|Avalugg}}\n\n==Trivia==\n* Avalugg has the highest base {{stat|Defense}} stat of all {{type|Ice}} Pokémon.\n* Avalugg shares its {{pkmn|category}} with {{p|Regice}}. They are both known as the Iceberg Pokémon.\n* Avalugg is the [[List of Pokémon with unique base stat totals|only Pokémon]] with a base stat total of 514.\n\n===Origin===\nAvalugg appears to be based on a {{wp|tabular iceberg}} or a {{wp|stalactite}}. It may be a representation of the submerged part of the iceberg, which is immense in comparison with the tip. Avalugg\'s {{t|Ice}} type and being likened to an {{wp|aircraft carrier}} may be a reference to {{wp|Project Habakkuk}}, a plan conceived by the {{wp|Allies of World War II|Allies}} in {{wp|World War II}} to build an aircraft carrier from {{wp|pykrete}}, a combination of ice and wood pulp. Its body also resembles an {{wp|aetosaur}}, or possibly a {{wp|tortoise}}.\n\n====Name origin====\nAvalugg may be a combination of \'\'avalanche\'\' and \'\'lug\'\' (to carry or drag heavy objects, or a big/clumsy person).\n\nCrebase may be a combination of \'\'{{wp|crevasse}}\'\' and \'\'base\'\'.\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=ice|type2=ice\n|ja=クレベース \'\'Crebase\'\'|jameaning=Possibly from \'\'{{wp|crevasse}}\'\' and \'\'base\'\'\n|fr=Séracrawl|frmeaning=From \'\'{{wp|serac|sérac}}\'\' and \'\'crawl\'\'\n|es=Avalugg|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Arktilas|demeaning=From \'\'{{wp|Arctic|Arktis}}\'\' and possibly \'\'{{wp|Attila}}\'\'\n|it=Avalugg|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=크레베이스 \'\'Keurebeiseu\'\'|komeaning=Based on its Japanese name; {{tt|\'\'crevasse\'\'|크레바스}} and {{tt|\'\'base\'\'|베이스}}\n|zh_yue=冰岩怪 \'\'Bīngngàahmgwaai\'\